      "content": "Please do not give aspirin to your 8-year-old. Aspirin can be very dangerous for children and can cause a rare but serious condition called Reye's syndrome. Instead, use acetaminophen (like Tylenol) or ibuprofen (like Motrin or Advil) made for children's dosage. Be sure to check the package directions carefully to ensure you are using the correct dosage for his age and weight. If his fever is very high or he seems significantly worse, call your pediatrician.",
